Mr. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bush</ENAMEX> said that he initiated talks with the <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Soviets</ENAMEX> on the informal meeting by sending a proposal to Mr. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Gorbachev</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">last July</ENAMEX> , which the <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Soviet</ENAMEX> leader readily accepted .
But word of the possible session was closely held by the president and a handful of top aides , and word of it did n't reach many <ENAMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">second</ENAMEX> - level officials until <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">the past few days</ENAMEX> .
